name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: The Florida Department of Health in Marion County would like to wish you and yours a Happy Thanksgiving on Thursday. We also remind you that our offices will be closed on Nov. 25 and 26. We will resume normal operations on Nov. 29. Have a great holiday!  https://t.co/zqdct3NImP

name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: As Marion County residents prepare to celebrate Thanksgiving, our friends at Marion County Fire Rescue offer some helpful advice on staying safe for those who prefer to deep fry their turkeys.  https://t.co/AwHwo2egLI

name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: A reminder: just because your bird looks done doesn't mean it is done. Don't let an undercooked turkey ruin your holiday.

name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: Today is the annual Great American Smokeout. Think about quitting smoking today. @tobaccofreefla can help you learn more about how to do that. Visit  https://t.co/JIK2RkG0Xb.  https://t.co/anU9T4H3Db

name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: Annually in Marion County injuries kill about 20 people age 19 or younger. At noon today, on #NationalInjuryPreventionDay, Dr @robinpetroze of @UFHealth offers advice on keeping kids safe with a free webinar. To sign up or learn more, go to  https://t.co/Hz6YP5FuF2. #BeInjuryFree

name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: Injury is the 3rd leading cause of death among kids in the US. Nov. 18 is #NationalInjuryPreventionDay, and DOH-Marion wants to help save lives. We ask people to wear green on 11/18 to do that, and to learn more about keeping kids safe @  https://t.co/AeNlkfxUgm.   #BeInjuryFree  https://t.co/33cWt9kd5d

name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: It's #DiabetesAwarenessMonth, and a good time to share that DOH-Marion and Marion County Hospital District are jointly hosting a free diabetes education class. The 6-week program starts Jan. 19 at the Fort McCoy public library. For more info, call 352-644-2624 or 352-438-2560  https://t.co/pF9eSQNTzC

name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: We can show you how to better protect your most precious cargo by using a car seat properly. From 5:30-7:30 p.m., Nov. 18, DOH-Marion offers a free class for families receiving any type of aid and needing a new car seat. You must register in advance. To do so, call 352-644-2751.  https://t.co/2XCoC9v3sf

name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: The DOH-Marion will begin offering Pfizer's children's  vaccine to youngsters ages 5 to 11 on Nov. 15. To learn more, including how to schedule an appointment, go here:  https://t.co/Mo6feBJFVO  https://t.co/rafwu4IiKr

name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: DOH-Marion wants to thank all of those who served in defense of our great nation, and to remind the public that all of our offices will be closed on Thursday, Nov. 11, in observance of Veterans Day. We will resume normal operations on Nov. 12.  https://t.co/FasVhZCuWw

name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: The CDC says 80% of Alzheimer’s patients receive care at home from family or friends, who then face greater risk of anxiety & depression. If you know a caregiver, show them your support this month during #NationalFamilyCaregiversMonth. Learn more@  https://t.co/AnowTTJebu  https://t.co/iR3oYEJJnt

name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: DYK Marion County has the highest death rate from diabetes for Florida counties with more than 100K residents? November is #DiabetesAwarenessMonth, and so it is a good time to visit DOH-Marion’s link at  https://t.co/zf8tY9UxKI and take our test to gauge your risk. #DefeatDiabetes  https://t.co/bGHdJ4fkSo

name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: DOH-Marion joined other partners with the Cancer Alliance of Marion County to accept a proclamation from the County Commission recognizing #LungCancerAwarenessMonth. The intent was to encourage using low-dose computed tomography, or LDCT, screening as an early-detection tool.  https://t.co/2caSjGBoaE

name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: Too much sugar can cause tooth decay. So if you're thinking about that Halloween candy, DOH-Marion’s dental program can help. We offer many primary-care services for insured and uninsured patients. To learn more, call 352-622-2664 or click here:  https://t.co/NePhA7fcIR.  https://t.co/6tuxhgWTDX

name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: In 2019, 17% of Marion County adults had been told at some point they had diabetes. That was the 9th-highest ratio in Florida. Since today is the start of #AmericanDiabetesMonth, visit DOH-Marion’s link to learn more about your risk of diabetes:  https://t.co/AO1GrNt83C  https://t.co/i8QTllGFwC

name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: Halloween approaches, a reminder the holidays are near. Also a time to consider a flu shot. DOH-Marion offers free flu shots for kids to age 19. Just visit our office, 1801 SE 32nd Ave. in Ocala, from 8am-4pm, Monday thru Friday. No appointment needed. For more info, 352-629-0137  https://t.co/NLk6BYt3HK

name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: Each year strokes kill nearly 200 Marion County residents and send almost 1,600 more to the hospital. Today, on #WorldStrokeDay, learn more about stroke, its risk factors and prevention tips. The Florida Department of Health can help. Visit here:  https://t.co/EgQJ8ixHhM.  https://t.co/UUtWBhwnLN

tweet: Reserva la fetcha! En 1/20/22 el Healthy Start Coalition of North Central Florida una assosciacion que incluye el Programa Healthy Start en el DOH–Marion, es el anfitrion de la “El Mejor Baby Shower del Mundo” un evento gratis para padres nuevos o futuros.  https://t.co/Srv1JiM35m

tweet: Save the date! name: Department of Health in Marion County
tweet: Outdated & unused prescription drugs can be risky. Clear the medicine chest and let the Marion County Sheriff, Ocala PD, or Dunnellon PD help you dispose of them on Oct. 23, #TakeBackDay, 10am-2pm, or 1pm at OPD. Learn more here:  https://t.co/6CrhqjSOFf
